<h2>Basic example</h2>
<p>The most basic list group is an unordered list with list items and the proper classes. Build upon it with the options that follow, or with your own CSS as needed.</p>
<div class="bs-example">
  {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET list-group-demo }}
  <BsListGroup as |ListGroup|>
    <ListGroup.item>An item</ListGroup.item>
    <ListGroup.item>A second item</ListGroup.item>
    <ListGroup.item>A third item</ListGroup.item>
  </BsListGroup>
  {{! END-SNIPPET }}
</div>
<div class="highlight">
  <CodeSnippet @name="list-group-demo.hbs" />
</div>

<h2>Flush</h2>
<p>Add <code>flush</code> to remove some borders and rounded corners to render list group items edge-to-edge in a parent container (e.g., cards).</p>
<div class="bs-example">
  {{! BEGIN-SNIPPET list-group-flush-demo }}
  <BsListGroup @flush={{true}} as |ListGroup|>
    <ListGroup.item>An item</ListGroup.item>
    <ListGroup.item>A second item</ListGroup.item>
    <ListGroup.item>A third item</ListGroup.item>
  </BsListGroup>
  {{! END-SNIPPET }}
</div>
<div class="highlight">
  <CodeSnippet @name="list-group-flush-demo.hbs" />
</div>

<h2>Numbered</h2>
